TESTNG GROUPS - INCLUDE AND EXCLUDE

1. INCLUDE GROUP

The `<include>` tag is used to execute only the test methods that belong to a specific group.

Syntax:

```xml
<groups>
    <run>
        <include name="Sanity"/>
    </run>
</groups>
```

Explanation:

* Wherever the group "Sanity" is present, those test methods will execute.
* Test methods belonging only to other groups will not execute.

Example:

```java
@Test(groups = {"Sanity"})
public void m1(){}

@Test(groups = {"Regression"})
public void m2(){}

@Test(groups = {"Regression","Sanity"})
public void m3(){}
```

If you include the "Sanity" group:

Methods Executed:

* m1()
* m3()

Methods Skipped:

* m2()

---

2. EXCLUDE GROUP

The `<exclude>` tag is used to skip all test methods that belong to a specific group.

Syntax:

```xml
<groups>
    <run>
        <exclude name="Regression"/>
    </run>
</groups>
```

Explanation:

* All methods belonging to the "Regression" group will be skipped.
* Only methods that do not belong to the Regression group will execute.

Example:

```java
@Test(groups = {"Sanity"})
public void m1(){}

@Test(groups = {"Regression"})
public void m2(){}

@Test(groups = {"Regression","Sanity"})
public void m3(){}
```

Methods Executed:

* m1()

Methods Skipped:

* m2() (Regression)
* m3() (Regression + Sanity)

Important:
If a test method belongs to both "Regression" and "Sanity", and you exclude "Regression", that method will also be skipped because it belongs to the excluded group.

---

3. INCLUDE AND EXCLUDE TOGETHER

Syntax:

```xml
<groups>
    <run>
        <include name="Sanity"/>
        <exclude name="Regression"/>
    </run>
</groups>
```

Explanation:

* TestNG first selects all methods belonging to the "Sanity" group.
* It then removes any methods that also belong to the "Regression" group.

Final Result:

* Only methods that belong exclusively to the "Sanity" group will execute.
* Methods that belong to both "Sanity" and "Regression" will not execute.

Interview Point:

* TestNG group names are case-sensitive.
* "Sanity" and "sanity" are considered different groups.
* A test method belonging to multiple groups is executed only once, even if multiple included groups match.
